ent-AU14GrenadeHighExplosiveUPP = Type 6 fragmentation grenade
    .desc = An outdated UNMC Fragmentation Grenade. With decades of service in the UNMC, the old M15 Fragmentation Grenade is slowly being replaced by the slightly safer 30mm-series grenades. It is set to detonate in 4 seconds.
    .suffix = UPP

ent-AU14GrenadeIncendiaryUPP = Type 8 incendiary grenade
    .desc = The 30mm High-explosive-Incendiary, Anti-Mobility grenade is a small, but deceptively strong incendiary grenade designed to disrupt enemy mobility with long-lasting Type B napalm. It is set to detonate in 4 seconds.
    .suffix = UPP

ent-AU14GrenadeSmokeUPP = RDG-17 smoke grenade
    .desc = The 30mm HSDP is a small, but powerful smoke grenade. Based off the same platform as the 30mm HEDP. It is set to detonate in 1 second.
    .suffix = UPP
